      "span_text": "Because a large fraction of cell biomass of the system was in the bead matrix (ca. 11 CFU g -1 beads after colonization) at the beginning of the fermentation, a higher number of adapted cells was expected in the gel beads, which were physically retained in the reactor, than in effluent at the end of culture."
